db694c49-b07f-40bf-abfa-be54d0ead839.title: Captain Rovin
db694c49-b07f-40bf-abfa-be54d0ead839.text:
What are you doing up here? Only the palace guards
are allowed up here.

options.text: I am one of the palace guards.
What about the King?
Yes I know, but this is important.

c93cbdad-42cc-49d6-8cca-1dc47242e063.title: <player>
c93cbdad-42cc-49d6-8cca-1dc47242e063.text: Yes, I know, but this is important.

0f9c8c3b-5f95-4a04-b2ea-9f9756710db8.title: Captain Rovin
0f9c8c3b-5f95-4a04-b2ea-9f9756710db8.text: Ok, I'm listening. Tell me what's so important.

options.text: Erm I forgot.
The castle has just received its ale delivery.
There's a demon who wants to invade this city.
Erm I forgot.
The castle has just received its ale delivery.

6437d03a-767d-480a-aa26-2c2e696e30d7.title: Captain Rovin
6437d03a-767d-480a-aa26-2c2e696e30d7.text: Well it can't be that important then.

88d328bf-bd66-47e3-9a8d-387d82ff9fbb.title: <player>
88d328bf-bd66-47e3-9a8d-387d82ff9fbb.text: I am one of the palace guards.

ce2f369a-5c9d-4463-b446-1b30f6c0e6da.title: Captain Rovin
ce2f369a-5c9d-4463-b446-1b30f6c0e6da.text: No, you're not! I know all the palace guards.

options.text: I'm a new recruit.
I've had extensive plastic surgery.

ca3d680b-213e-4c73-9134-ea1b7ba3dcd6.title: Captain Rovin
ca3d680b-213e-4c73-9134-ea1b7ba3dcd6.text:
I interview all the new recruits. I'd know if you were
one of them.

7498d975-e870-487b-952c-83cc8ae3563e.title: <player>
7498d975-e870-487b-952c-83cc8ae3563e.text: That blows that story out of the water then.

aca5e726-ef77-4e3d-ae97-c09c11adf681.title: Captain Rovin
aca5e726-ef77-4e3d-ae97-c09c11adf681.text:
What sort of surgery is that? I've never heard of it.
Besides, you look reasonably healthy.

a9f3a5e7-d669-429e-b7b5-1c87c8190ea5.title: Captain Rovin
a9f3a5e7-d669-429e-b7b5-1c87c8190ea5.text:
Why is this relevant anyway? You still shouldn't be
here.

bf06cdb7-4a4b-4b37-8e1b-b34aac95a994.title: <player>
bf06cdb7-4a4b-4b37-8e1b-b34aac95a994.text: What about the King? Surely you'd let him up here.

033a7e08-6457-4f0d-b046-6b9b149c5433.title: Captain Rovin
033a7e08-6457-4f0d-b046-6b9b149c5433.text:
Well, yes, I suppose we'd let him up. He doesn't
generally want to come up here, but if he did want to,
he could.

31555723-d4b5-4382-a536-12897eb07109.title: Captain Rovin
31555723-d4b5-4382-a536-12897eb07109.text:
Anyway, you're not the King either. So get out of my
sight.

ffcaf244-040a-4cf3-a73b-1eb9aa1c6f3f.title: <player>
ffcaf244-040a-4cf3-a73b-1eb9aa1c6f3f.text: The castle has just received its ale delivery.

1f571494-d172-430f-855d-4226881751ac.title: Captain Rovin
1f571494-d172-430f-855d-4226881751ac.text:
Now that is important. However I'm the wrong person
to speak to about it. Go talk to the kitchen staff.

624ca176-638d-4cf9-a1f1-109169a28b52.title: <player>
624ca176-638d-4cf9-a1f1-109169a28b52.text: There's a demon who wants to invade the city.

options.text: Not really.
Yes, very.

9d5f7be0-6d0d-42af-ae2e-fc52576f31c5.title: Captain Rovin
9d5f7be0-6d0d-42af-ae2e-fc52576f31c5.text:
Well, I'm sure the palace guards can deal with it, then.
Thanks for the information.

36b42c83-fd6e-400a-9f95-7d2565fd2508.title: Captain Rovin
36b42c83-fd6e-400a-9f95-7d2565fd2508.text:
As good as the palace guards are, I don't know if
they're up to taking on a very powerful demon.

options.text: Yeah, the palace guards are rubbish!
It's not them who are going to fight the demon, it's me.

12f3183c-d7e3-4667-82fd-d499a2ef9cbc.title: <player>
12f3183c-d7e3-4667-82fd-d499a2ef9cbc.text: Yeah, the palace guards are rubbish!

83676176-39ac-45bf-bf47-20cb2229ab76.title: Captain Rovin
83676176-39ac-45bf-bf47-20cb2229ab76.text:
Wait! How dare you insult the palace guards? Get out
of my sight!

2e38defe-b994-4f42-931b-eb4dd58b736f.title: <player>
2e38defe-b994-4f42-931b-eb4dd58b736f.text: It's not them who are going to fight the demon, it's me.

9912a036-f01f-4f3b-861c-a5b532d9b421.title: Captain Rovin
9912a036-f01f-4f3b-861c-a5b532d9b421.text: What, all by yourself? How are you going to do that?

810918e9-bebc-405a-bc8d-4360a54a0c68.title: <player>
810918e9-bebc-405a-bc8d-4360a54a0c68.text:
I'm going to use the powerful sword Silverlight, which I
believe you have one of the keys for?

b8e23ab3-0d4a-4da1-a8d4-2a39b880a80e.title: Captain Rovin
b8e23ab3-0d4a-4da1-a8d4-2a39b880a80e.text: Yes, I do. But why should I give it to you?

options.text: Gypsy Aris said I was destined to kill the demon.
Otherwise the demon will destroy the city!
Sir Prysin said you would give me the key.

1f7a539d-f2f4-435f-b831-bbf951e82327.title: <player>
1f7a539d-f2f4-435f-b831-bbf951e82327.text: Otherwise the demon will destroy the city!

3394458d-97a0-4bdc-97fd-75b3ca748eb1.title: Captain Rovin
3394458d-97a0-4bdc-97fd-75b3ca748eb1.text:
You can't fool me! How do I know you haven't just
made that story up to get my key?

options.text: Gypsy Aris said I was destined to kill the demon.
Sir Prysin said you would give me the key.

f5a2af51-eb6b-4df2-b148-68eac0cc0786.title: <player>
f5a2af51-eb6b-4df2-b148-68eac0cc0786.text: Gypsy Aris said I was destined to kill the demon.

0cbccd08-785a-496a-a70a-118acaea9508.title: Captain Rovin
0cbccd08-785a-496a-a70a-118acaea9508.text:
A gypsy? Destiny? I don't believe in that stuff. I got
where I am today by hard work, not by destiny! Why
should I care what that mad old gypsy says?

options.text: Otherwise the demon will destroy the city!
Sir Prysin said you would give me the key.

00b18b2c-54db-4acd-abbb-bb72c7436c18.title: <player>
00b18b2c-54db-4acd-abbb-bb72c7436c18.text: Sir Prysin said you would give me the key.

85317ddd-b3f2-4dce-b5e2-41fba20bcb57.title: Captain Rovin
85317ddd-b3f2-4dce-b5e2-41fba20bcb57.text:
Oh, he did, did he? Well I don't report to Sir Prysin, I
report directly to the king!

11e79353-d375-465d-af1c-954b76d4518e.title: Captain Rovin
11e79353-d375-465d-af1c-954b76d4518e.text:
I didn't work my way up through the ranks of the
palace guards so I could take orders from an ill-bred
moron who only has his job because his great-
grandfather was a hero with a silly name!

options.text: Why did he give you one of the keys then?
Gypsy Aris said I was destined to kill the demon.
Otherwise the demon will destroy the city!

e9d2cafb-b7f6-4239-8076-80066b395be6.title: <player>
e9d2cafb-b7f6-4239-8076-80066b395be6.text: Why did he give you one of the keys then?

cf83b925-1429-4323-b7f0-1b465ddfeea6.title: Captain Rovin
cf83b925-1429-4323-b7f0-1b465ddfeea6.text:
Only because the king ordered him to! The king
couldn't get Sir Prysin to part with his precious
ancestral sword, but he made him lock it up so he
couldn't lose it.

ff708524-ff08-484f-a0c1-0915aea1a3d8.title: Captain Rovin
ff708524-ff08-484f-a0c1-0915aea1a3d8.text:
I got one key and I think some wizard got another.
Now what happened to the third one?

5f83d9f3-1c01-436f-b2a0-19d4e34ceed9.title: <player>
5f83d9f3-1c01-436f-b2a0-19d4e34ceed9.text: Sir Prysin dropped it down a drain!

8021a086-37ca-4376-8905-3644a62868b7.title: Captain Rovin
8021a086-37ca-4376-8905-3644a62868b7.text:
Okay, I'll give you the key, just so that it's you that
kills the demon and not Sir Prysin!

0de75682-3134-41bf-b479-a026f1501894.text: Captain Rovin hands you a key.
